ciscoLispExtMIB.name: ciscoLispExtMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the CISCO-LISP-EXT-MIB module.

ciscoLispExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: lisp-support@cisco.com
ciscoLispExtMIB.description: This MIB is an extension to the IETF LISP-MIB module defined in RFC 7052. It contains Cisco defined managed objects and traps to support monitoring devices that support the Locator/ID Separation Protocol (LISP).

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipTable.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipTable
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipTable.description: This table lists the RLOC address gleaned from the map-server registration database for the purpose of RLOC membership. Entry on this table can also be added from configuration.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEntry.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEntry
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEntry.description: An entry describes an RLOC address gleaned from the map-server registration database.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipInstanceID.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipInstanceID
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipInstanceID.description: This object indicates the instance ID of the RLOC address.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEidAfi.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEidAfi
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipEidAfi.description: This object indicates the IANA Address Family Identifier of the RLOC address.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRlocLength.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRlocLength
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRlocLength.description: This object indicates the length of the RLOC address.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRloc.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRloc
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipRloc.description: This object indicates the value of the RLOC address.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipMemberSince.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipMemberSince
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipMemberSince.description: This object indicates the sysUpTime when this RLOC address was registered. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGleaned.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGleaned
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGleaned.description: This object indicates whether the RLOC address was gleaned from a received EID prefix registration. If this object is true, then it means the RLOC address was gleaned.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipConfigured.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipConfigured
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipConfigured.description: This object indicates whether the RLOC address was added by configuration. If this object is true, then it means the RLOC address was configured.

clispExtRlocMembershipTable.name: clispExtRlocMembershipTable
clispExtRlocMembershipTable.description: This table lists the RLOC membership learned by the xTR. Entry can be learned from the map-server or from configuration.

clispExtRlocMembershipEntry.name: clispExtRlocMembershipEntry
clispExtRlocMembershipEntry.description: An entry describes the RLOC membership learned by the xTR.

clispExtRlocMembershipInstanceID.name: clispExtRlocMembershipInstanceID
clispExtRlocMembershipInstanceID.description: This object indicates the instance ID of the RLOC membership.

clispExtRlocMembershipEidAfi.name: clispExtRlocMembershipEidAfi
clispExtRlocMembershipEidAfi.description: This object indicates the IANA Address Family Identifier of the RLOC membership.

clispExtRlocMembershipRlocLength.name: clispExtRlocMembershipRlocLength
clispExtRlocMembershipRlocLength.description: This object indicates the length of the RLOC membership.

clispExtRlocMembershipRloc.name: clispExtRlocMembershipRloc
clispExtRlocMembershipRloc.description: This object indicates the value of the RLOC membership.

clispExtRlocMembershipMemberSince.name: clispExtRlocMembershipMemberSince
clispExtRlocMembershipMemberSince.description: This object indicates the sysUpTime when the RLOC membership was added. If this information was present at the most recent reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

clispExtRlocMembershipDiscovered.name: clispExtRlocMembershipDiscovered
clispExtRlocMembershipDiscovered.description: This object indicates whether the RLOC membership was learned from the map-server. If this object is true, then it means the RLOC membership was learned.

clispExtRlocMembershipConfigured.name: clispExtRlocMembershipConfigured
clispExtRlocMembershipConfigured.description: This object indicates whether the RLOC membership was added by configuration. If this object is true, then it means the RLOC membership was configured.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionTable.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionTable
clispExtReliableTransportSessionTable.description: This table lists the reliable transport sessions. The session may or may not be in established state.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionEntry.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionEntry
clispExtReliableTransportSessionEntry.description: An entry describes the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddr.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddressLength
clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddr.description: This object indicates the length of the reliable transport session peer address.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddr.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddress
clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerAddr.description: This object indicates the peer address of the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerPort.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerPort
clispExtReliableTransportSessionPeerPort.description: This object indicates the peer port of the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAdd.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAddressLength
clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAdd.description: This object indicates the length of the reliable transport session local address.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAdd.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAddress
clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalAdd.description: This object indicates the local address of the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalPor.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalPort
clispExtReliableTransportSessionLocalPor.description: This object indicates the local port of the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionState.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionState
clispExtReliableTransportSessionState.description: This object indicates the state of the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionLastStat.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionLastStateChangeTime
clispExtReliableTransportSessionLastStat.description: This object indicates the sysUpTime of the last UP/DOWN state transition on the reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionEstablis.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionEstablishmentRole
clispExtReliableTransportSessionEstablis.description: This object indicates the role of the reliable transport session. 'active' Connection was initiated locally by the LISP router. 'passive' Connection was accepted by the LISP router listening on the well-known local transport port.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessages.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessagesIn
clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessages.description: This object indicates the number of messages received on this reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessages.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessagesOut
clispExtReliableTransportSessionMessages.description: This object indicates the number of messages sent on this reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesIn.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesIn
clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesIn.description: This object indicates the number of bytes received on this reliable transport session.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesOut.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesOut
clispExtReliableTransportSessionBytesOut.description: This object indicates the number of bytes sent on this reliable transport session.

clispExtGlobalStatsTable.name: clispExtGlobalStatsTable
clispExtGlobalStatsTable.description: This table lists statistic to augment the lispGlobalStatsTable.

clispExtGlobalStatsEntry.name: clispExtGlobalStatsEntry
clispExtGlobalStatsEntry.description: An entry containing additional global statistics information.

clispExtGlobalStatsEidRegMoreSpecificEnt.name: clispExtGlobalStatsEidRegMoreSpecificEntryCount
clispExtGlobalStatsEidRegMoreSpecificEnt.description: This object indicates the number of EID prefix registration that are accepted as a result of the accept-more-specific configuration.

clispExtFeaturesTable.name: clispExtFeaturesTable
clispExtFeaturesTable.description: This table contains additional LISP feature entries for lispFeaturesTable.

clispExtFeaturesEntry.name: clispExtFeaturesEntry
clispExtFeaturesEntry.description: An entry containing additional LISP feature information.

clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarnin.name: clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThreshold
clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarnin.description: This object indicates the warning threshold for the accept-more-specific registration count on the map-server.

clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimit.name: clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimit
clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimit.description: This object indicates the accept-more-specific registration limit on the map-server.

clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThreshold.name: clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThreshold
clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThreshold.description: This object indicates the map-cache warning threshold on the xTR.

clispExtEidRegFailureCause.name: clispExtEidRegFailureCause
clispExtEidRegFailureCause.description: This object indicates the cause of the map registration failure on the map-server. 'noEidPrefixConfiguration' No site configuration to accept registration for EID prefix. 'authenticationFailure' Failed to authenticate map-register for EID prefix. 'allowedLocatorMismatch' map-register contains RLOC that is not in the site's allowed locator list.

clispExtEidRegMapRequestDroppedCause.name: clispExtEidRegMapRequestDroppedCause
clispExtEidRegMapRequestDroppedCause.description: This object indicates the cause of the map-request drop on the map-resolver. 'malformedRequest' map-request is not valid. 'noMatchingEidRegistration' could not find matching EID registration for the map-request. 'allowedLocatorPolicyViolation' map request does not conform to the configured allowed-locator policy.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresho.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThreshold
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresho.description: This object indicates the warning threshold for the accept-more-specific registration count on the map-server. This warning threshold is applicable to all EID instances.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimit.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimit
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimit.description: This object indicates the accept-more-specific registration limit on the map-server. This is applicable to all EID instances.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificCount.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificCount
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificCount.description: This object indicates the number of map registrations accepted as a result of accept-more-specific configuration. This is applicable to all EID instances.

clispExtUseMapResolverStateChange.name: clispExtUseMapResolverStateChange
clispExtUseMapResolverStateChange.description: The device generates this notification when the map-resolver reachability state changes. The lispUseMapResolverAddressLength and lispUseMapResolverAddress values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtReliableTransportStateChange.name: clispExtReliableTransportStateChange
clispExtReliableTransportStateChange.description: The device generates this notification when the reliable transport session state changes. The clispReliableTransportSessionPeerAddressLength, clispReliableTransportSessionPeerAddress, clispReliableTransportSessionPeerPort, clispReliableTransportSessionLocalAddressLength, clispReliableTransportSessionLocalAddress, clispReliableTransportSessionLocalPort values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtMappingDatabaseEidRegFailure.name: clispExtMappingDatabaseEidRegFailure
clispExtMappingDatabaseEidRegFailure.description: The device generates this notification when the xTR fails to register a database mapping with the map-server. The lispMappingDatabaseEidLength, lispMappingDatabaseEid, lispUseMapServerAddressLength, lispUseMapServerAddress values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtUseMapServerStateChange.name: clispExtUseMapServerStateChange
clispExtUseMapServerStateChange.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server reachability state changes. The lispUseMapServerAddressLength and lispUseMapServerAddress values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtUseProxyEtrStateChange.name: clispExtUseProxyEtrStateChange
clispExtUseProxyEtrStateChange.description: The device generates this notification when the proxy ETR reachability state changes. The lispUseProxyEtrAddressLength and lispUseProxyEtrAddress values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtEidRegSiteAllRegistrationsExpire.name: clispExtEidRegSiteAllRegistrationsExpired
clispExtEidRegSiteAllRegistrationsExpire.description: The device generates this notification when all the registration for a site expires on the map-server. The lispEidRegistrationEidLength and lispEidRegistrationEid values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtEidRegFailure.name: clispExtEidRegFailure
clispExtEidRegFailure.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server fails to accept a map registration. The lispEidRegistrationEidLength and lispEidRegistrationEid values are attached to the notification object ID. If clispExtEidRegFailureCause value is noEidPrefixConfiguration(1) the lispEidRegistrationSiteName object in the notification will be empty.

clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimitR.name: clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimitReached
clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificLimitR.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server has reached the limit of the number of map registrations it can accept as a result of the accept-more-specific configuration. This notification is instance specific. The lispFeaturesInstanceID and lispFeaturesAddressFamily values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarnin.name: clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresholdReached
clispExtFeaturesEidRegMoreSpecificWarnin.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server has reached the threshold of the number of map registrations it can accept as a result of accept-more-specific configuration. This notification is instance specific. The lispFeaturesInstanceID and lispFeaturesAddressFamily values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtEidRegMapRequestDropped.name: clispExtEidRegMapRequestDropped
clispExtEidRegMapRequestDropped.description: The device generates this notification when the map-resolver drops a map-request because the map-request does not conform to configured policy. The lispEidRegistrationEidLength and lispEidRegistrationEid values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimitReached.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimitReached
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificLimitReached.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server has reached the limit of the number of map registrations it can accept as a result of the accept-more-specific configuration. This notification is router LISP instance specific.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresho.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresholdReached
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificWarningThresho.description: The device generates this notification when the map-server has reached the threshold of the number of map registrations it can accept as a result of accept-more-specific configuration. This notification is router LISP instance specific.

clispExtFeaturesMapCacheLimitReached.name: clispExtFeaturesMapCacheLimitReached
clispExtFeaturesMapCacheLimitReached.description: The device generates this notification when the xTR has reached the limit of the number of map-cache it can create. This notification is instance specific. The lispFeaturesInstanceID and lispFeaturesAddressFamily values are attached to the notification object ID.

clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThreshold.name: clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThresholdReached
clispExtFeaturesMapCacheWarningThreshold.description: The device generates this notification when the xTR has reached the threshold of the number of map-cache it can create. This notification is instance specific. The lispFeaturesInstanceID and lispFeaturesAddressFamily values are attached to the notification object ID.

ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceAll.name: ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceAll
ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceAll.description: Compliance requirement for implementations of CISCO-LISP-EXT-MIB by all LISP (P)xTR devices. Map-server database of gleaned RLOC addresses only need to be supported on LISP Map Server.

ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceMapServer.name: ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceMapServer
ciscoLispExtMIBComplianceMapServer.description: Compliance requirement for implementations of CISCO-LISP-EXT-MIB by LISP Map Server devices.

clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGroup.name: clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGroup
clispExtEidRegRlocMembershipGroup.description: A collection of objects to support reporting MapServer database of RLOC membership.

clispExtRlocMembershipGroup.name: clispExtRlocMembershipGroup
clispExtRlocMembershipGroup.description: A collection of objects to support reporting RLOC membership information.

clispExtReliableTransportSessionGroup.name: clispExtReliableTransportSessionGroup
clispExtReliableTransportSessionGroup.description: A collection of objects to support reporting \ ReliableTransportSession information.

clispExtGlobalStatsGroup.name: clispExtGlobalStatsGroup
clispExtGlobalStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects to support reporting \ Cisco define augments to the lispGlobalStatsTable

clispExtFeaturesGroup.name: clispExtFeaturesGroup
clispExtFeaturesGroup.description: A collection of objects to support reporting \ Cisco define augments to the lispFeaturesTable.

clispExtNotificationSupportGroup.name: clispExtNotificationSupportGroup
clispExtNotificationSupportGroup.description: A collection of objects to be supplied within notifications.

clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificValuesGroup.name: clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificValuesGroup
clispExtEidRegMoreSpecificValuesGroup.description: A collection of objects to be supplied within notifications.
